  "prompt": "Can anyone help me with writing the RC6 algorithm for Visual Basic 6?",
  "response": "Certainly! RC6 is a symmetric key block cipher derived from RC5. The algorithm involves key expansion, encryption, and decryption. Below is a simplified version of RC6 implemented in Visual Basic 6. Note that this implementation assumes a fixed block size of 128 bits and a key size of 128 bits.\n\nThe code is broken down into several parts: key expansion, encryption, and decryption. For simplicity, I'll provide a basic structure for each part.\n\n### Key Expansion\n\n```vb\nOption Explicit\n\n' Constants\nPrivate Const w As Integer = 32\nPrivate Const r As Integer = 20\nPrivate Const Pw As Long = &HB7E15163\nPrivate Const Qw As Long = &H9E3779B9\n\n' Key schedule array\nDim S(0 To 2 * r + 3) As Long\n\n' Key Expansion function\nPublic Sub KeyExpansion(ByVal key As String)\n    Dim L((Len(key) + 3) / 4 - 1) As Long\n    Dim i As Integer, j As Integer\n    Dim A As Long, B As Long\n    Dim u As Integer, t As Integer, v As Integer\n\n    ' Initialize L array\n    For i = 0 To (Len(key) / 4) - 1\n        L(i) = Asc(Mid(key, i * 4 + 1, 1)) Or (Asc(Mid(key, i * 4 + 2, 1)) * &H100&) Or _\n               (Asc(Mid(key, i * 4 + 3, 1)) * &H10000&) Or (Asc(Mid(key, i * 4 + 4, 1)) * &H1000000&)\n    Next i\n\n    ' Initialize S array\n    S(0) = Pw\n    For i = 1 To 2 * r + 3\n        S(i) = S(i - 1) + Qw\n    Next i\n\n    ' Mix the secret key into the S array\n    i = 0\n    j = 0\n    A = 0\n    B = 0\n    For k = 0 To 3 * (2 * r + 4) - 1\n        S(i) = RotateLeft(S(i) + A + B, 3)\n        A = S(i)\n        L(j) = RotateLeft(L(j) + A + B, (A + B) Mod 32)\n        B = L(j)\n        i = (i + 1) Mod (2 * r + 4)\n        j = (j + 1) Mod (Len(key) / 4)\n    Next k\nEnd Sub\n\n' Rotate left function\nPrivate Function RotateLeft(ByVal x As Long, ByVal y As Integer) As Long\n    RotateLeft = ((x << y) Or (x >> (w - y))) And &HFFFFFFFF\nEnd Function\n```\n\n### Encryption\n\n```vb\nPublic Sub Encrypt(ByVal plaintext As String, ByRef ciphertext As String)\n    Dim A As Long, B As Long, C As Long, D As Long\n    Dim t As Long, u As Long, x As Long\n    Dim i As Integer\n\n    ' Divide plaintext into four 32-bit words\n    A = Asc(Mid(plaintext, 1, 1)) Or (Asc(Mid(plaintext, 2, 1)) * &H100&) Or _\n        (Asc(Mid(plaintext, 3, 1)) * &H10000&) Or (Asc(Mid(plaintext, 4, 1)) * &H1000000&)\n    B = Asc(Mid(plaintext, 5, 1)) Or (Asc(Mid(plaintext, 6, 1)) * &H100&) Or _\n        (Asc(Mid(plaintext, 7, 1)) * &H10000&) Or (Asc(Mid(plaintext, 8, 1)) * &H1000000&)\n    C = Asc(Mid(plaintext, 9, 1)) Or (Asc(Mid(plaintext, 10, 1)) * &H100&) Or _\n        (Asc(Mid(plaintext, 11, 1)) * &H10000&) Or (Asc(Mid(plaintext, 12, 1)) * &H1000000&)\n    D = Asc(Mid(plaintext, 13, 1)) Or (Asc(Mid(plaintext, 14, 1)) * &H100&) Or _\n        (Asc(Mid(plaintext, 15, 1)) * &H10000&) Or (Asc(Mid(plaintext, 16, 1)) * &H1000000&)\n\n    ' Initial round\n    B = B + S(0)\n    D = D + S(1)\n\n    ' Main rounds\n    For i = 1 To r\n        t = RotateLeft(B * (2 * B + 1), 5)\n        u = RotateLeft(D * (2 * D + 1), 5)\n        A = RotateLeft(A Xor t, u) + S(2 * i)\n        C = RotateLeft(C Xor u, t) + S(2 * i + 1)\n\n        x = A\n        A = B\n        B = C\n        C = D\n        D = x\n    Next i\n\n    ' Final round\n    A = A + S(2 * r + 2)\n    C = C + S(2 * r + 3)\n\n    ' Combine the words back into the ciphertext\n    ciphertext = Chr(A And &HFF) & Chr((A >> 8) And &HFF) & Chr((A >> 16) And &HFF) & Chr((A >> 24) And &HFF) & _\n                 Chr(B And &HFF) & Chr((B >> 8) And &HFF) & Chr((B >> 16) And &HFF) & Chr((B >> 24) And &HFF) & _\n                 Chr(C And &HFF) & Chr((C >> 8) And &HFF) & Chr((C >> 16) And &HFF) & Chr((C >> 24) And &HFF) & _\n                 Chr(D And &HFF) & Chr((D >> 8) And &HFF) & Chr((D >> 16) And &HFF) & Chr((D >> 24) And &HFF)\nEnd Sub\n```\n\n### Decryption\n\n```vb\nPublic Sub Decrypt(ByVal ciphertext As String, ByRef plaintext As String)\n    Dim A As Long, B As Long, C As Long, D As Long\n    Dim t As Long, u As Long, x As Long\n    Dim i As Integer\n\n    ' Divide ciphertext into four 32-bit words\n    A = Asc(Mid(ciphertext, 1, 1)) Or (Asc(Mid(ciphertext, 2, 1)) * &H100&) Or _\n        (Asc(Mid(ciphertext, 3, 1)) * &H10000&) Or (Asc(Mid(ciphertext, 4, 1)) * &H1000000&)\n    B = Asc(Mid(ciphertext, 5, 1)) Or (Asc(Mid(ciphertext, 6, 1)) * &H100&) Or _\n        (Asc(Mid(ciphertext, 7, 1)) * &H10000&) Or (Asc(Mid(ciphertext, 8, 1)) * &H1000000&)\n    C = Asc(Mid(ciphertext, 9, 1)) Or (Asc(Mid(ciphertext, 10, 1)) * &H100&) Or _\n        (Asc(Mid(ciphertext, 11, 1)) * &H10000&) Or (Asc(Mid(ciphertext, 12, 1)) * &H1000000&)\n    D = Asc(Mid(ciphertext, 13, 1)) Or (Asc(Mid(ciphertext, 14, 1)) * &H100&) Or _\n        (Asc(Mid(ciphertext, 15, 1)) * &H10000&) Or (Asc(Mid(ciphertext, 16, 1)) * &H1000000&)\n\n    ' Initial round\n    C = C - S(2 * r + 3)\n    A = A - S(2 * r + 2)\n\n    ' Main rounds\n    For i = r To 1 Step -1\n        x = D\n        D = C\n        C = B\n        B = A\n        A = x\n\n        u = RotateLeft(D * (2 * D + 1), 5)\n        t = RotateLeft(B * (2 * B + 1), 5)\n        C = RotateRight(C - S(2 * i + 1), t) Xor u\n        A = RotateRight(A - S(2 * i), u) Xor t\n    Next i\n\n    ' Final round\n    D = D - S(1)\n    B = B - S(0)\n\n    ' Combine the words back into the plaintext\n    plaintext = Chr(A And &HFF) & Chr((A >> 8) And &HFF) & Chr((A >> 16) And &HFF) & Chr((A >> 24) And &HFF) & _\n                Chr(B And &HFF) & Chr((B >> 8) And &HFF) & Chr((B >> 16) And &HFF) & Chr((B >> 24) And &HFF) & _\n                Chr(C And &HFF) & Chr((C >> 8) And &HFF) & Chr((C >> 16) And &HFF) & Chr((C >> 24) And &HFF) & _\n                Chr(D And &HFF) & Chr((D >> 8) And &HFF) & Chr((D >> 16) And &HFF) & Chr((D >> 24) And &HFF)\nEnd Sub\n```\n\n### Usage Example\n\n```vb\nPublic Sub EncryptDecryptExample()\n    Dim key As String\n    Dim plaintext As String\n    Dim ciphertext As String\n\n    key = \"your_secret_key\"\n    plaintext = \"your_plain_text\"\n\n    ' Key expansion\n    Call KeyExpansion(key)\n\n    ' Encryption\n    Call Encrypt(plaintext, ciphertext)\n    Debug.Print \"Ciphertext: \" & ciphertext\n\n    ' Decryption\n    Call Decrypt(ciphertext, plaintext)\n    Debug.Print \"Plaintext: \" & plaintext\nEnd Sub\n```\n\n### Note\n- This code assumes that the plaintext and ciphertext are exactly 128 bits (16 bytes). You'll need to handle padding and block management for longer messages.\n- This code is simplified and may lack optimizations and extensive error checks.\n- RC6 is patented, so ensure you have the proper rights to use it in your applications.\n\nThis should give you a basic structure to work with RC6 in Visual Basic 6. You may need to adjust and optimize based on your specific requirements.",
